<br>

## Dinosaurs
Dinosaurs are among the oldest reptiles in the world. Predatory dinosaurs are savage, territorial hunters. Herbivorous dinosaurs are less aggressive, but they might attack to defend their young, or if startled or harassed.

Dinosaurs come in many sizes and shapes with a large variety of colorations and markings between them. They roam many regions of Azeroth, including remote mountain valleys, humid jungles, and rugged barren plains.

### Raptor
The raptor is an aggressive theropods predator of great strength and speed. It can run down almost any prey over open ground, pouncing to pull creatures down with its wicked claws and fanged maw.

### Threshadon
A plesiosaurus is a marine dinosaur whose compact body is driven by powerful flippers. Predatory and aggressive, it attacks any creature it encounters. Its flexible neck accounts for a third of its total length, letting it twist in any direction to deliver a powerful bite.

