## Trogg
Troggs are savage creatures, powerfully built with long and muscular arms. They often have beards and their muscle appear to have been carved in stone; it is not rare to see minerals growing out of their flesh. Troggs have an apelike posture, which makes them be associated with troglodytes.

***Fierce and primitive.*** Troggs are often related with Gnomes, since in the recent history they have been burrowed into the lowest levels in Gnomeregan. Troggs are twice the size of a gnome and much physically stronger. They are drived only from primal insticts like hunger and thirst for power, so the biggest and strongest in a tribe often becomes chieftain; it is not rare to see them consume stone and everything they can, including other troggs. They are known to be cunning in battle but without possessing high intelligence they depend instead on their ferocity. There are only a few which are intelligent enough to become spell casters and learn to speak a language like Low Common.

***Undergound creatures.*** Most troggs do not like sunlight and prefere dig tunnels under the earth using their jagged claws or tools made out of rocks, which they use also to make axes, arrows and small utensils.

___
> ## Trogg
>*Medium humanoid (trogg), chaotic evil*
> ___
> - **Armor Class** 13 (natural armor)
> - **Hit Points** 26 (5d8 + 6)
> - **Speed** 30 ft.
